              <span id="reviewTextContainer3827419731" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15161630910277238479">*Score: 5/10*<br/><br/>This is a series of 5 letters from a Portuguese nun to her French lover who has abandoned her, and it shows the anger and frustration of a lost love and the feeling of betrayal from a nun&apos;s prespective.<br/><br/>This was written in the 1600s, and its actually not clear if it was written directly by the nun herself (Mariana), or if this is fiction written by the French Politician Gabriel de Guilleragues about this nun (who has definitely been a real person). <br/><br/>Regardless, this is a short 1 hr re</span>
  <span id="freeText15161630910277238479" style="display:none">*Score: 5/10*<br /><br />This is a series of 5 letters from a Portuguese nun to her French lover who has abandoned her, and it shows the anger and frustration of a lost love and the feeling of betrayal from a nun's prespective.<br /><br />This was written in the 1600s, and its actually not clear if it was written directly by the nun herself (Mariana), or if this is fiction written by the French Politician Gabriel de Guilleragues about this nun (who has definitely been a real person). <br /><br />Regardless, this is a short 1 hr read, not much here other than the interesting historical context, language is good but gets very annoying as it repeats over and over the same frustrations of the nun. Very forgettable.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15161630910277238479" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
